               <anchor type="scribe"/> 
               <seg type="pers" subtype="scribe">comāciyāṇṭ<lb type="2" n="98r6"/>āṉ <hi
                  rend="grantha">vaṃśa</hi>m āṉa <placeName ref="place:0000X">tiruṉārāyaṇapuratt</placeName>(') aṟaiyar <persName ref="pers:0000X" role="scribe">ciṅkarācāriyar</persName></seg>
               
               <anchor type="copFor"/>
               <seg type="copFor-end" subtype="eluti-muki">eḻunt(') aruḷappaṇṇi mukiñcitu</seg> ||</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="traslation">
            <head>Translation</head>
            <p>On the day of the year Cātāraṇam, [month of] Arpici, bright fortnight, day nine,
               Friday, Ciṅkarācāriyar, priest (aṟaiyar) of Tiruṉārāyaṇapuram, who is in the lineage
               of Comāciyāṇṭāṉ, finished copying this manuscript of the Tirumantrārttham, which is
               the Svarūpopāyapuruṣārttham.</p>
         </div>
